methods.containsNonNormal:
Returns true if the values contains any non-normal value, where "normal" is defined as
 not infinite, not NaN, and not null.

*Overload 1*  
  :param values: (java.lang.Float...) - values.
  :return: (boolean) true if any value is not normal; false otherwise.
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param values: (float[]) - values.
  :return: (boolean) true if any value is not normal; false otherwise.
methods.isInf:
Returns true if the value is infinite and false otherwise.

:param value: (float) - value.
:return: (boolean) true if the value is infinite and false otherwise.
methods.isNaN:
Returns true if the value is NaN and false otherwise.

:param value: (float) - value.
:return: (boolean) true if the value is NaN and false otherwise.
methods.isNormal:
Returns true if the value is normal, where "normal" is defined as not infinite, not NaN, and not null.

:param value: (float) - value.
:return: (boolean) true if the value is not infinite, NaN, nor null; false otherwise

text: A set of commonly used floating point numeric functions that can be applied to Float types.
